50|$|According to the Thai monk Venerable Buddhadsa Bhikku's writing, ‘India's Benevolence to Thailand’, the Thais also {{obtained}} {{the methods of}} making herbal medicines from the Indians. Some plants like Sarabhi of Guttiferae family, Kanika or <b>hursinghar,</b> phikun or mimusops and bunnak or the rose chestnut etc. were brought from India. He pointed out that Thai food too was influenced by India. He claimed that Thai people learned how to use spices in their food in various ways from Indians.|$|E

